    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="683" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">von Holleben</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6,
                                1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state for your
                            information that I am in receipt of a telegram of the 6th instant from
                            the U. S. vice consul-general at Apia, which reads as follows:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>Chief justice notified by consuls. Refuses compliance with directions
                                of three powers respecting survey and register fees.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
